encodingDesc.p:
In this version I have tried to standardize the more useful distinctions which I think the
    original typography intended to convey, as follows: 

Titles of works, usually given in single quotes, are tagged using title;

Terms of art originally given in quotes, or indicated as such by italics, such as `debut'
      or `original' are tagged using term; 

Verbatim quotations from contemporary reviews are tagged using q; 

Phrases identifying the source of a contemporary review are tagged using
      cite;

Dates or dating expressions given in parenthesis are tagged using date;

Role names, actor names, names of theatres etc. are not currently distinguished.
